To-Do List App
To-Do List Flask API
This is a Flask-based API for managing tasks. It supports CRUD operations for task resources and uses Flask-Migrate for database migrations. The API interacts with a database to store and retrieve tasks and includes features for handling user data, task categories, and user-task associations.

Technologies Used
Flask: A lightweight Python web framework for building APIs.
Flask-RESTful: An extension for Flask that simplifies the creation of REST APIs.
Flask-Migrate: Handles SQLAlchemy database migrations.
Flask-CORS: A Flask extension for handling Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS).
dotenv: Loads environment variables from a .env file.
SQLAlchemy: ORM for handling database interactions.
SQLAlchemy-Serializer: A library to serialize SQLAlchemy models to JSON.
Installation
Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/todo-backend.git
cd Events